I have been learning more about understanding each component of the process


Such as a piece of code in python to spin up Flask for example,

from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def hello():
    return 'Hello, Flask!'

if __name__ == '__main__':
    # debug=True restarts on code changes; host='0.0.0.0' makes it reachable on your LAN
    app.run(debug=True, host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)


Also using Postman to obtain code to be able to create java classes that can interact with flask

import java.io.IOException;
import okhttp3.OkHttpClient;
import okhttp3.Request;
import okhttp3.Response;

public class OkHttpGet {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        OkHttpClient client = new OkHttpClient();

        // Build the GET request
        Request request = new Request.Builder()
            .url("https://api.example.com/data?param=value")
            .addHeader("Accept", "application/json")
            // .addHeader("Authorization", "Bearer <token>")
            .get()
            .build();

        // Execute and handle response
        try (Response response = client.newCall(request).execute()) {
            System.out.println("Status code: " + response.code());
            if (response.body() != null) {
                System.out.println("Response body:\n" + response.body().string());
            }
        } catch (IOException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Then learning more about how to parse JSON information with object mapping in JackSON for example

ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
MyData data = mapper.readValue(response.body(), MyData.class);

